---
title: "From repro film to Claude: 25 years of design tools, and what never changed"
excerpt: I've watched four technology waves hit this craft - desktop publishing, the web, smartphones, and now AI. Each one was declared the death of design. Here's what actually died each time, what survived, and why the surviving part is always the same.
date: '2026-08-13'
category: Studio
